  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Retrospective study, single-center, on 171 patients, presented a cryptogenic TIA and Minor
      stroke.

      This study objective is to determine profitability of Holter 21 days for screening paroxystic
      ACFA / flutter in cryptogenic TIA/Minor stroke, and identify the predictive factors of
      discovery a paroxystic ACFA on Holter 21 days. Clinical and Ã©chocardiographics factors, and
      brain imaging (scanner and MRI) will be analyzed.
    </textblock>
